# Ruleprediction-agent (prediction engine & briefing)

**Alias:** **`/ruleprediction-agent`** = **`/ruler-prediction-agent`** — same rule; use this filename only.

## Scope

Applies when editing **`prediction_agent/`**, **`scripts/prediction_horizon_check.py`**, **`finance_agent/http_main.py`**, **`.cursor/agents/prediction-agent.md`**, **`docker/Dockerfile.btc_trader`**, or **`letscrash/RULE_AND_DATA_FLOW_LOOP.md`** / **`letscrash/BTC_TRADER_DOCKER.md`**.

## Consult other agents (set rules with correct data flows)

Before changing **Docker**, **compose**, or **.mdc** rules for prediction/BTC pipelines, cross-check:

| Surface | Path |
|---------|------|
| **prediction-agent** | `.cursor/agents/prediction-agent.md` |
| **market-data** (on-chain/daily bundle) | `.cursor/agents/market-data.md` |
| **btc-specialist** (Bybit + `btc_specialist/`) | `.cursor/agents/btc-specialist.md` |
| **finance-agent** (briefing, `bot.py`) | `.cursor/agents/finance-agent.md` |
| **Worker inherit** | `.cursor/rules/sygnif-agent-inherit.mdc` |
| **Predict workflow** | `.cursor/rules/sygnif-predict-workflow.mdc` |

**Long-form loop + indicator wishlist + btc_Trader_Docker I/O table:** **`letscrash/RULE_AND_DATA_FLOW_LOOP.md`** — rules **evolve**; that file is the canonical narrative for the **continuous information → train → propose → prove → test → rm/apply → compare** cycle.

## Ports (do not fragment)

- **Finance-agent HTTP** defaults to **`FINANCE_AGENT_HTTP_PORT=8091`** (see `finance_agent/bot.py`). **`GET /briefing`**, sentiment, overseer hooks share this listener — avoid a second ad-hoc HTTP server for the same contract.

## RAM / CPU

- Run **at most one** heavy train job (runner, Hydra `cryptopredictions`, PyTorch submodule) at a time on small instances.
- Keep **`btc_predict_runner.py`** windows bounded via CLI; do not load full history into briefing responses.

## Self-learning (bounded)

- **Mechanical feedback:** `scripts/prediction_horizon_check.py` (`save` / `check`) — no live orders.
- **Retrain:** prefer systemd timer + logs; document disk and peak RAM.
- **Live risk:** only via **`user_data/strategy_adaptation.json`** (clamped keys) or explicit strategy integration + tests — never imply `prediction_agent` drives Freqtrade by default.

## Honesty

- `prediction_agent/SOURCES.md`: BitVision / CryptoPredictions extracts are **reference** unless explicitly wired.
- Delegate narrative TA parity to **`finance_agent/bot.py`** / **SygnifStrategy** — not duplicated here.
